{"name":"Cascade Lance (Melee)","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Originally thought to be an ornate staff for melee combat, an accidental (and devastating) activation revealed it also fires a tightly focused beam of exotic particles with enough power to melt tank hulls and reduce living creatures to ash. A cascade lance requires two hands to wield when it is used as a melee weapon.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":6,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+6","damageType":"energy","penetration":"8","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Concussive (1), Power Field","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/barbed-spear.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2X9lOix4yzYiijZ5"}
{"name":"Havatian Ringblade (Melee)","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A subterranean and secretive species that existed on but a few Thule Sub-Sector planets, the Havat only appeared a few times in Askellian history. Most know of the xenos from the ringblade, a strange chakram with a corrosive liquid core. Both a melee weapon and a grenade, some believe the Havat used the liquid within the ring to create and maintain their underground civilisation. A character may use a Havatian ringblade as a melee weapon or as a grenade. If used as a grenade, it explodes on impact and is destroyed.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":1,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"rending","penetration":"3","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Razor Sharp","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/lightning-saber.svg","effects":[],"_id":"7e1oyVcqE0NLmpAr"}
{"name":"Big Choppa","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Big choppas go a step beyond the basic choppa design, often incorporating all manner of whirring saws, unstable energy fields, and sharpened metal &ldquo;teef&rdquo; bolted into the blades. They are most often used by Ork Nobz, who proudly swing their big choppas against friend and foe alike with wild abandon. A big choppa is a two-handed weapon. At the GM&rsquo;s discretion, it can have the Power Field quality; if it does, it should also have the Overheats quality.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":10,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Tearing, Unbalanced","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/battered-axe.svg","effects":[],"_id":"7sU1bzyzSUnebD3w"}
{"name":"Molecular Blade","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Featuring an oddly shaped blade that extends from either side of the grip, a molecular blade appears to flicker in and out of reality, and corrodes anything it hits.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":15,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"5","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Corrosive, Razor Sharp, Tearing","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/blade-drag.svg","effects":[],"_id":"A8tKsgrAh5kNDWkM"}
{"name":"Eldar Power Sword","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A sleek, elegant weapon that puts the designs of any Askellian forge world to shame, an Eldar power sword&rsquo;s keen balance and lightweight grip makes it an excellent duelling blade. It is often seen as a sign of status amongst Rogue Traders as well as Ordo Xenos Inquisitors in the sector to possess one, either as a gift from alien partners or as spoils from battle.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":1,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+5","damageType":"energy","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Balanced, Power Field","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/pointy-sword.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Fh9dfU8A3I0LWqsY"}
{"name":"Burna (Melee)","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A terrifying weapon of surprising sophistication&mdash;at least by Ork standards&mdash;it combines a highly volatile flamer with a dangerous short-ranged cutting torch. Useful for everything from herding squigs to carving holes in hull plating, burnas fulfil a variety of roles within Ork society. The burna has two profiles (one for melee and one for ranged combat), and requires two hands to use in either mode. Its weight includes the backpack fuel tank.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":8,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"5","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Power Field, Unwieldy","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/axe-sword.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RSDOttxLYhfHRsZ4"}
{"name":"Agoniser","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A weapon capable of inflicting unrelenting torment, the agoniser usually takes the form of a barbed whip made from an unknown xenos material. Rare even in the hands of the most Radical Inquisitors or their most vicious of Acolytes, it overloads a target&rsquo;s nervous systems with each cruel lash, inflicting gruesome neural damage regardless of the target&rsquo;s size or protection. When a character suffers Critical damage from an attack with a Best craftsmanship agoniser, his Perception characteristic is also permanently reduced by 1d5.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":2,"class":"melee","type":"","range":3,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"energy","penetration":"6","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Flexible, Power Field, Tearing, Shocking","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/whip.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WZjBp8yS5vHYCWDf"}
{"name":"Choppa","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The Choppa is the quintessential Ork weapon and takes on many different forms, from massive hatchets, to heavy machetes, to rudimentary analogues of chainswords. Virtually every Ork owns a choppa of some description, and its above-average lethality makes it more than just a simple melee weapon. For any non-Ork character with a Strength bonus of 3 or less, a choppa requires two hands to wield.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":1,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+1","damageType":"rending","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Unbalanced","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/machete.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YPCBYlF5wddYuD8F"}
{"name":"Harlequinâ€™s Kiss","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Very few within the Askellon Sector have witnessed the horrifyingly destructive power of the Harlequin&rsquo;s Kiss, but the weapon&rsquo;s reputation is well-known. The signature weapon of the inscrutable Harlequins, the weapon takes the form of a long tube protruding from the forearm. When struck against a target it expels a strand of monofilament that quickly finds any exposed flesh or armour breach. Once it penetrates the flesh, the alien filament unspools, liquefying organs and shredding internal machinery in seconds. Rare by Eldar standards, let alone the Imperium&rsquo;s, it is a weapon of high prestige, even among those that frown upon the use of xenos technology.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":1,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+8","damageType":"rending","penetration":"10","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Felling (4), Tearing, DMG-SB","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/stiletto.svg","effects":[],"_id":"k8hxgngQZR7vCgPE"}
{"name":"Talonblade","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Crafted from the cruel talons of a still-unknown species, these blades are growing in use across the Asphodel Depths, worrying many Ordo Xenos Inquisitors. They are prized by hunters and pitfighters alike for their perpetual sharpness and the ugly wounds they produce.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":1,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"rending","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Razor Sharp, Tearing","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/blade-drag.svg","effects":[],"_id":"so5hlsaFaamKd4Te"}
